cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of parallel graph algorithms on GPUs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance variation of different BFS implementations across different graphs. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper aims to improve the performance of graph traversal algorithms. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper focuses on GPU-based graph traversal. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation and tuning of different graph operations on GPUs.
